From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: peter <peter@navq.local>
Date: Thu, 26 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dedup: include <cstdint> for fixed-width integer types

GCC 15 / newer libstdc++ no longer transitively includes <cstdint> via
<memory>, so dedup.h fails to compile with "uint32_t has not been
declared" / "uint8_t does not name a type". Include <cstdint> explicitly.

Upstream-Status: Pending [to be submitted to mavlink-router]
---
 src/dedup.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/dedup.h b/src/dedup.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/src/dedup.h
+++ b/src/dedup.h
@@ -16,6 +16,7 @@
 #pragma once
 
 #include <memory>
+#include <cstdint>
 
 class DedupImpl;
 
